race.comment: TAINUI (1) raced on the speed but compounded in the run home last start over this distance at Scone. Kody Nestor gets the best out of this gelding and he goes back on today. Best form measures up nicely so certainly worth another chance today with the blinkers removed. Veteran DAWN COUNTY (2) won three from four prior to a last start failure over 1400m at Coonabarabran. His last run at this distance was three back at Narromine where he scored with plenty in reserve. This looks a nice race. The recent efforts of BLUE GUITAR (5) in open company mile races have been just fair. Draws in a bit closer this time and Mathew Cahill going on is a tick. Watch for sharp improvement. Consistent mare MRS BULL (6) doesn't win too often but recent efforts have been sound. Up in class but this distance specialist gets all the favours from the inside stall and represents good each-way value. SUBUKI (4) is in the mix dropping back to a more favourable journey.
